#
#  WHAT CHANGED (high level):
#   * Removed the cmd.load/cmd.fetch monkeypatch that ran center('all') on
#     EVERY load (the O(N^2) "gets laggy after a while" bug).
#   * pgup/pgdn cycle structures WITHOUT resetting the camera (no orient()).
#   * Backbone color is no longer "stuck": coloring is done via atom colors and
#     cartoon_color is left at default, so `color red, myobj` just works.
#   * New switchable, journal-quality color schemes (white bg by default):
#         scheme_ipd (default) | scheme_vivid | scheme_graphite | scheme_foliage(legacy)
#   * ALWAYS-ON, per object, on load: catalytic residues (REMARK 666) shown as
#     accent sticks; metals (by ELEMENT, not resn) shown as spheres; current
#     scheme applied.  Toggle with `autostyle off`.
#   * New commands: seq, only_catres, catres (selection), bg_white/bg_black,
#     catres_style A|B, restyle, autostyle, pymolrc_help.
#   * Loading is faster: async_builds (threaded geometry), deferred builds,
#     max_threads for ray tracing, no per-load global recenter.
# ============================================================================

